HEADWORD: Directoire style
<hw>Di`rec`toire" style</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Dressmaking)</fld>
<def>A style of dress prevalent at the time of the French Directory,
characterized by great extravagance of design and imitating the Greek
and Roman costumes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

